  "text": "Kubernetes implements lease-based leader election in client-go/tools/leaderelection/. The core is LeaderElector.Run() which calls acquire() then renew(). acquire() loops calling tryAcquireOrRenew() which uses a Kubernetes Lease object (via LeaseLock) as a distributed lock\u2014Get/Create/Update on coordination/v1 Lease resources. Failover happens when the leader fails to renew within LeaseDuration; other candidates detect the expired lease and atomically update it. leasecandidate.go adds the newer Coordinated Leader Election (alpha). etcd implements Raft-based leader election in the raft/ library (raft.go, node.go). The core flow is: tickElection() fires on followers when the election timeout elapses, triggering hup() \u2192 campaign() \u2192 becomeCandidate() \u2192 vote solicitation. On quorum vote, becomeLeader() transitions state and stepLeader() handles leader message processing. tickHeartbeat() on the leader sends periodic heartbeats; if checkQuorum detects lost quorum, the leader steps down via becomeFollower(). Leader transfer is handled by MsgTransferLeader in stepLeader() which sends MsgTimeoutNow to the transferee. The etcd server layer (server/etcdserver/raft.go and server.go) wraps the raft Node, handling leadership changes in the raftNode.start() goroutine, and exposes MoveLeader()/TryTransferLeadershipOnShutdown() for graceful leader transfer. etcd also provides a higher-level client election API (client/v3/concurrency/election.go and server/etcdserver/api/v3election/election.go) built on etcd leases and key ordering.",
